---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Terms of Service" 
  description="TravelWithPola's terms of service - booking conditions, cancellation policy, and travel guidelines."
>
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 bg-gradient-to-b from-nile-900 to-nile-800">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-nile-200">Last updated: December 2024</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="py-16 bg-papyrus-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-lg prose-stone">
      <h2>1. Booking and Reservations</h2>
      <p>
        All bookings are subject to availability and confirmation. A deposit may be required to secure your reservation. Full payment is typically due 30 days before the trip start date.
      </p>
      
      <h2>2. Cancellation Policy</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>30+ days before departure:</strong> Full refund minus processing fee</li>
        <li><strong>15-29 days before departure:</strong> 50% refund</li>
        <li><strong>7-14 days before departure:</strong> 25% refund</li>
        <li><strong>Less than 7 days:</strong> No refund</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We strongly recommend purchasing travel insurance.</p>
      
      <h2>3. Changes to Itinerary</h2>
      <p>
        While we make every effort to operate trips as planned, we reserve the right to make changes to itineraries due to weather, safety concerns, local conditions, or circumstances beyond our control.
      </p>
      
      <h2>4. Traveler Responsibilities</h2>
      <p>Travelers are responsible for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Obtaining valid travel documents (passport, visa)</li>
        <li>Ensuring adequate health and travel insurance</li>
        <li>Following guide instructions and safety guidelines</li>
        <li>Respecting local customs and laws</li>
        <li>Arriving on time for scheduled activities</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2>5. Health and Fitness</h2>
      <p>
        Some tours involve walking on uneven surfaces, climbing stairs, and exposure to heat. Please inform us of any health conditions that may affect your participation.
      </p>
      
      <h2>6. Liability</h2>
      <p>
        TravelWithPola acts as an agent for third-party service providers. While we carefully select our partners, we cannot be held liable for their acts or omissions. We are not responsible for losses due to circumstances beyond our control.
      </p>
      
      <h2>7. Photography</h2>
      <p>
        We may take photographs during tours for promotional purposes. Please inform us if you prefer not to be photographed.
      </p>
      
      <h2>8. Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any complaints during your trip, please inform your guide immediately so we can address the issue. Written complaints should be submitted within 28 days of trip completion.
      </p>
      
      <h2>9. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by Egyptian law. Any disputes will be resolved through Egyptian courts.
      </p>
      
      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about these terms, contact us at:<br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:info@travelwithpola.com">info@travelwithpola.com</a><br>
        Phone: +20 123 456 7890
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

